      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-antesonic-condition-and-magnetocentrifugal-winds&#34;&gt;The Antesonic Condition and Magnetocentrifugal Winds&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matthias J Raives | 21 Oct 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;the-antesonic-condition&#34;&gt;The Antesonic Condition&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pejcha &amp;amp; Thompson (2012) found that, for an isothermal equation of state, the Euler equations and the shock-jump conditions cannot be simultaneously satisfied when&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$\frac{c_T^2}{v_{\rm esc}^2} \geq \frac{3}{16}$&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;at the shock.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-antesonic-condition-1&#34;&gt;The Antesonic Condition&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As $c_T$ increases, the shock moves out to larger radii, until no shocked solution can be found&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;section&gt; (image1) &lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section&gt; (image2) &lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section&gt; (image3) &lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section&gt; (image4) &lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section&gt; (image5) &lt;/section&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;time-dependent-simulations&#34;&gt;Time-Dependent Simulations&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;section&gt;&lt;font size=&#34;6&#34;&gt;In time-dependent simulations, when the antesonic condition is exceeded, the accretion flow undergoes a time-dependent transition into a wind solution.  We identify this transition with the supernova explosion.
&lt;p&gt;(image)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/section&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
