&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-supernova-critical-condition&#34;&gt;The Supernova Critical Condition&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;section&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;container&#34;&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;col&#34;&gt;
During the steady state accretion phase, there is some $\dot{M}$ and some $L_{\nu,\rm core}$, set by progenitor properties and fundamental physics.
&lt;p&gt;Burrows &amp;amp; Goshy (1993) showed that steady accretion is only possible below a certian &amp;ldquo;critical&amp;rdquo; $L_{\nu,\rm core}^{\rm crit}(\dot{M})$.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;col&#34;&gt;


















