&lt;div class=&#34;col&#34;&gt;
Neutrino mechanism cannot power high luminosity events like GRBs and SLSNe.
&lt;p&gt;Magnetocentrifugal forces dominate proto-neutron star winds&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rapid magnetic braking can taps huge reservoir of rotational energy — B field forces co-rotation out to Alfvén radius $R_A\gg R_0$.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But&amp;hellip; &lt;span class=&#34;fragment &#34; &gt;
existing models assume 2D axisymmetry, dipole spindown, and cannot simulate long timescales
