&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;summary&#34;&gt;Summary&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=container&gt;
&lt;div class=col&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Why do supernovae explode?&lt;/b&gt; Steady-state shocked accretion flow becomes impossible.  The flow must transition into a wind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;What role does turbulence play in aiding explosion?&lt;/b&gt; Turbulence lowers the critical sound speed required for explosion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;How do proto-magnetars spin down after birth?&lt;/b&gt; My models account for tilt between the rotation and magnetic axes.  They can  simulate to late times and do not assume dipole spindown. I provide $\dot{E}(t)$, $\dot{J}(t)$ across a wide parameter space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
